---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const buildDate = new Date().toISOString().slice(0, 10).replace(/-/g, '.');
---
<Layout
  title="About"
  description="What Intent Alpha is, how it works, and what it isn't."
  spineGlyph="¶"
  bgEquation="α : t ↦ Σ signals(t)"
>
  <section class="hero" style="border-bottom: 0; padding-bottom: 1.5rem;">
    <span class="meta meta--accent">Colophon</span>
    <h1>What this is.</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      Intent Alpha reads the public job postings of leading technology companies and infers
      what they are building next. Each dispatch is an explicit, falsifiable hypothesis.
    </p>
  </section>

  <article class="prose" style="margin-top: 2rem;">
    <h2>Method</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>We pull job postings from public ATS endpoints — Greenhouse, Lever, Workday.</li>
      <li>We track changes over time — what roles appear, disappear, and cluster.</li>
      <li>From those patterns, a single hypothesis is proposed per cycle.</li>
      <li>The hypothesis is then audited against pre-registered fail/pass criteria before publication.</li>
      <li>Each dispatch ships with an explicit confidence label and horizon.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>What this is not</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Not investment advice.</li>
      <li>Not insider information &mdash; everything is sourced from public listings.</li>
      <li>Not a guarantee &mdash; hypotheses are falsifiable by design.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Sources</h2>
    <p>
      Job postings are read from publicly accessible endpoints provided by the applicant
      tracking systems each company uses. We respect <code>robots.txt</code> and stated
      terms of service. Snapshots are version-controlled.
    </p>

    <h2>Cadence</h2>
    <p>
      This site is rebuilt and redeployed on every push to the source repository.
      Data analyses (cross-reference, vocab-shift, withdrawal-lifetime, diffusion-velocity)
      are recomputed against the latest snapshots and the outputs are committed back into
      the tree, so what you see and what the dispatches cite are the same files.
    </p>
    <p class="meta" style="margin-top: 1rem; text-transform: none; letter-spacing: 0;">
      Last build: <code>{buildDate}</code>
    </p>
  </article>
</Layout>
